NEWS: MOBILE-SYNC                                                   21.07.2012
===============================================================================

# 2.3 (21. July 2012)
Enhancements:
  - prints the current date and time using date function into a timestamp file.

# 2.2 (16. April 2012)
Bugfixes:
  - compress() function now compresses the archive based on file ending;
    the program tar is used now instead of bsdtar.

# 2.1 (29. February 2012)
Enhancements:
  - Added function isynch, which interactively lets you synchronize one folder
  - Added help option (only commandline) and text
  - Added adjustable timeout option
  - Added internable read_timeout option

ChangeLog:
  - Replacing all instances of 'echo' with 'printf', since we don't know what
    we are printing. (Could lead to subtle bugs).
  - Added function confirm, which confirms a question, to be used with if

